2)  essentially, they will work the same except the second one is a bit more 
    complicated.In the first statemant, if karl can pick something, it will turn right,  
    and if it cannot, it will turn left.
    In the second statement, if karl cannot pick somthin it will turn left and
    if karl can pick something it will also turn right. So basically, both the
    statements will the same except they are written opossitely.
